This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with the detection and classification of fake news messages from Twitter posts using deep learning techniques. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing social media data. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) may also be a likely sub-category as the paper involves identifying relevant features associated with fake news stories. Finally, the paper may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category as fake news can be used as a tool for cyber attacks.
